    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="811"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d811">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 European War 1939/1042</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-12">June 12,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Prime Minister<note n="97" xml:id="d811fn97">Emmanuel J. Tsouderos.</note>
                    and the Minister of Greece<note n="98" xml:id="d811fn98">Cimon P.
                        Diamantopoulos.</note> called and handed me some documents (copies
                        attached<note n="99" xml:id="d811fn99">The memorandum <hi rend="italic"
                            >infra</hi>, and its attachments (not printed).</note>) relative to the
                    views and attitude of Greece with respect to certain problems which
                    appropriately would come up at the end of the war. I thanked him and said that I
                    would receive them solely as information at present and not from the standpoint
                    of giving consideration to them at this time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ull</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
